2026-04-21 01:31:32 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['connection between power supply module and control module'] hypothesis_explanation='The symptoms are: power-supply LED on (PSU delivering 12 V), control-module red LED on (indicating reversed polarity at its input), proper polarity and continuity between control-module output and load-module input, and the lamp not working. A test confirmed that the PSU +12 V line is connected to the control module’s 0 V input terminal and the PSU 0 V line to the control module’s +12 V input terminal. An attempted ‘Adjust’ action to correct the wiring reported that the polarity inversion remains and that no persistent circuit-level changes were made. This indicates that the only real fault is a configuration error: the two cables between power supply and control are cross-connected (swapped) in the installed system. No internal component appears faulty; instead the inter-module wiring between the power supply module and control module is mis-connected and must be re-terminated so that PSU + goes to control + and PSU – goes to control –.'
