2026-04-21 01:31:58 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['control module switch', 'wiring between switch and Control Output Cable (+)'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show that the control module has a correct internal 12 V rail and that 12 V reaches the supply side of the switch (~11.99 V). However, the switch behaves as an open circuit with an extremely high resistance (~1×10⁹ Ω) instead of the expected low on‑resistance, and the Control Output Cable (+) is floating/disconnected on the load side. Downstream of the control module, the load‑module input and all internal load nodes remain at 0 V even with the switch operated. This is consistent with a failed‑open control switch or its immediate series wiring to the Control Output Cable (+), preventing 12 V from ever reaching the load. Replacing/repairing the switch and its series connection to the output should restore power delivery to the load module and allow the lamp to operate.'
